==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Duffel
<hw>Duf"fel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>duffel</ets>,
from <ets>Duffel</ets>, a town not far from Antwerp.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A kind of coarse woolen cloth, having a thick nap or frieze.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>duffle</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Good <qex>duffel</qex> gray and flannel fine.</q> <rj><qau>
Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Outfit or suppplies, collectively; kit.</def>
<mark>[Colloq., U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Duffel bag</ent>⟦br⟧
